Sharing and Visibility
The purpose of this section is to outline the record-level visibility and sharing controls applied across the various object tables defined within the Salesforce data model.

Account
The Organization-Wide Default (OWD) sharing setting for the Account object will be configured as Private. Account visibility will be driven by the territory configuration. Consequently, an Account assigned to a specific territory will be visible to users residing at that territory node, as well as those in all superior levels. For additional territory visibility, we would use Account Team Member if necessary.

More detail on: Territory Management

Account Team Member
The Account Team Member object will be utilized strictly as an internal backend mechanism to drive the sharing model. It will not be exposed to standard users; visibility and management of these configuration records will be restricted entirely to System Administrators

Standard & Custom Account Child Objects (General Rule)
For objects structurally dependent on the Account, such as Address, Account Business Unit, Sales Team, Account Relationship, Data Change Request, Data Change Request Field, Account Landscape, Account Segmentation, Account Plan, Asset, Sharepoint File, and Visit, records will be structured using a Master-Detail relationship to the Account object. Consequently, the sharing model for these is strictly Controlled by Parent; any user granted read access to an Account will implicitly inherit visibility to its associated records.

