Account Contact Relation
The visibility of the Account Contact Relation (ACR) object is inherently governed by its two parent records. As a standard junction object, its sharing model is strictly Controlled by Parent on both sides. Consequently, a user must possess at least Read access to both the associated Account and Contact to view the relationship record.

Contact
To accommodate the multi-account data model and streamline the system architecture, Contact visibility will be governed natively by Enterprise Territory Management (ETM). The Organization-Wide Default (OWD) for the Contact object will be set to Private.
Instead of relying on custom programmatic sharing or automated flows, the platform's standard ETM Contact Access level will be configured to: "View and edit all contacts associated with accounts in the territory, regardless of who owns the contacts."
This standard configuration ensures that any user assigned to a territory automatically inherits Read and Edit access to all Contacts related to the Accounts within that territory node. This architectural approach provides several key benefits:

Native Synchronization: It seamlessly supports multi-account structures and Account Contact Relations (ACR) without requiring custom ContactShare automations.
Scalability & Performance: It leverages Salesforce's out-of-the-box sharing recalculation engine, avoiding flow execution overhead and potential system limits.
Simplified Maintenance: Eliminates technical debt associated with custom sharing logic for the Contact object.
(Note: If specific fields on the Contact need to be protected from editing by users outside of a specific Business Unit, this will be handled via targeted Validation Rules rather than restricting the baseline ETM edit access).

Contact Segmentation
The Contact Segmentation will be configured with a Master-Detail relationship to the Contact object. Consequently, its sharing model is strictly Controlled by Parent, ensuring that any user with visibility to a specific Contact automatically inherits access to all of its related Contact Segmentation records.

Lead
The Organization-Wide Default (OWD) for the Lead object will be configured as Public Read/Write (or Public Read Only). An open visibility model is optimal for the initial prospecting phase to prevent duplicate records. Post-conversion, the resulting Account and Opportunity fall under the strict Enterprise Territory Management (ETM) security model.

Individual & Reference Catalogs
The Individual, Account Segmentation Reference, Master Preference, Preferences, Consent Traceability, Contact Point Data, and Data Use Purpose objects will be configured as Public Read Only. This guarantees global transparency for compliance, reference, and reporting across all territories.

Individual
The Individual object serves as the centralized repository for data privacy and marketing consent. Because it is linked to both Leads and Contacts via a standard Lookup relationship, it cannot natively inherit their sharing settings.

To ensure strict regulatory compliance across the platform, the Organization-Wide Default (OWD) for the Individual object will be configured as Public Read Only. This architectural decision guarantees that any user interacting with a newly created Lead or a territory-restricted Contact can seamlessly access the associated consent profile, preventing unauthorized communications without requiring complex, independent sharing rules.

Account Segmentation Reference
The Organization-Wide Default (OWD) for the Account Segmentation Reference object will be set to Public Read Only, ensuring that these master catalog values are visible to all users across the system.

However, to maintain data integrity during assignment, a Validation Rule will be enforced when associating these references to a specific Account. This control mechanism will dynamically restrict the selectable segmentation values, ensuring users can only associate reference records that belong to a Business Unit already related to that target Account.

Product
The Organization-Wide Default (OWD) for the Product object will be set to Public Read Only. This ensures that the entire product catalog is visible across the organization for reference and reporting purposes.

To manage the Business Unit segregation, the system will enforce Lookup Filters on the Opportunity Product and Order Request Item objects. These filters will dynamically restrict product selection, ensuring that users can only associate products that match the Business Unit of the parent Opportunity or Order Request.

Price Book & Price Book Entry
The sharing model for Price Books will be set to View Only by default.

While the Product catalog remains Public Read Only, the ability to apply pricing is strictly controlled via Price Book Entries.

To manage the Business Unit segregation, the system will enforce Lookup Filters on the Opportunity Product and Order Request Item objects. These filters will dynamically restrict product selection, ensuring that users can only associate products that match the Business Unit of the parent Opportunity or Order Request.

Master Preference
The Organization-Wide Default (OWD) for the Master Preference object will be set to Public Read Only, ensuring that these master catalog values are visible to all users across the system.

Preferences
The custom Preferences object will be configured with a Public Read Only Organization-Wide Default (OWD) sharing setting. Although this object is structurally related to the Lead or Contact via a Lookup relationship, its baseline visibility is deliberately kept open.

In practice, users will access these records contextually by navigating through the parent Lead or Contact. By maintaining a Public Read Only model, the architecture ensures that any user who successfully accesses the parent record can seamlessly view the associated communication and business preferences, while simultaneously guaranteeing global transparency for compliance reporting across all territories.

Contact Point Data
The custom Contact Point Data object will be configured with a Public Read Only Organization-Wide Default (OWD) sharing setting. Although this object is structurally related to the Lead or Contact via a Lookup relationship, its baseline visibility is deliberately kept open.

In practice, users will access these records contextually by navigating through the parent Lead or Contact. By maintaining a Public Read Only model, the architecture ensures that any user who successfully accesses the parent record can seamlessly view the associated contact point data records, while simultaneously guaranteeing global transparency for compliance reporting across all territories and preventing duplicate entries.

Consent Traceability
Since Contact Point Data are public, it makes sense that change control, traceability, and consent history should also be public.

Data Use Purpose
The sharing model for Data Use Purpose will be set to Public Read Only by default. This ensures that all records are visible across the organization for proper consent and record management in Contact Point Data.

Opportunity
The Organization-Wide Default (OWD) sharing setting for the Opportunity object will be configured as Private.

Read Access: Visibility will be inherited seamlessly from the Account. The Enterprise Territory Management (ETM) configuration will be set to grant users View access to all Opportunities associated with the Accounts in their territory.

Edit Access: To manage the Business Unit matrix, a Validation Rule will be implemented. While users can view all Opportunities for an Account, the validation rule will block any save/edit actions unless the user's designated Business Unit matches the Opportunity's Business Unit.

Opportunity Product, Opportunity Group, Opportunity Activity Relationship: Strictly Controlled by Parent.

Opportunity Team Member and Opportunity Contact Role: Inherently dictated by the parent Opportunity.

Opportunity Product
The Opportunity Product (OpportunityLineItem) object is natively structured as a strict Master-Detail child of the Opportunity. Consequently, its Organization-Wide Default (OWD) sharing setting is irrevocably Controlled by Parent.

This architecture ensures that any user who access to an Opportunity will implicitly inherit full visibility into all associated product lines, requiring no independent sharing configuration.

Opportunity Group
