Event
The Event object serves as the core record for managing events. It is a standalone custom object and does not inherit visibility from the Account territory model.

Organization-Wide Default (OWD): The sharing setting will be configured as Private.
Visibility Mechanism: Access is driven by Criteria-Based Sharing Rules leveraging the Sales Org field.
Access Logic: * Records are shared with Public Groups corresponding to each Sales Organization, ensuring users only see events relevant to their specific region.
Event Children (Controlled by Parent)
For objects structurally dependent on the Event, records will be configured using a Master-Detail relationship. Consequently, their sharing model is strictly Controlled by Parent; any user with access to an Event record will implicitly inherit visibility to its associated child records. This includes:

Task Participant
The custom Task Participant object will be configured with a Master-Detail relationship to the Event object (or Controlled by Parent standard equivalent).

Event Attendee
The custom Event Attendee object will be configured with a Master-Detail relationship to the Event object (or Controlled by Parent standard equivalent).

Event Expenses
The custom Event Expenses object will be configured with a Master-Detail relationship to the Event object (or Controlled by Parent standard equivalent).

Event Organization
The Event Organization object acts as a regional configuration table, defining attendance capacities and budget allocations per territory/region.

Organization-Wide Default (OWD): Private.

Visibility Mechanism: Similar to the Event object, visibility is governed by Criteria-Based Sharing Rules based on the Sales Organization.

Rationale: This ensures that sensitive budget configurations and regional constraints are only visible to the users operating within that specific Sales Org.

Fair Market Value
The FMV object is a compliance reference matrix that dictates spending limits and caps for attendees based on their professional tier or classification.

Organization-Wide Default (OWD): Private (or Public Read Only if global transparency is required, though restricted to Sales Org is recommended for regional compliance).

Visibility Mechanism: Access is granted via Criteria-Based Sharing Rules based on the Sales Organization.

Rationale: Since compliance regulations and spending limits vary significantly by country and Sales Organization, this model ensures users only apply the financial rules applicable to their specific jurisdiction.

