User Interface & Workspace Management (List Views)
To ensure that the open read-visibility model does not overwhelm users with irrelevant records from other Business Units, the User Interface will be heavily optimized using targeted List Views.

Business Unit Specific List Views: For objects like Opportunities, Business Activities, Order Requests, and Orders, specific List Views will be created, pre-filtered by Business Unit.
Targeted Sharing: These List Views will be shared exclusively with the corresponding Business Unit Public Groups.
Result: While a user can navigate to an Account and view a holistic picture of all records (Read Access), their day-to-day workspace (Tabs and List Views) will remain clean, prioritized, and strictly tailored to their specific Business Unit responsibilities.
Enterprise Territory Management (ETM) & Business Unit Security Configuration
This section outlines the specific configuration of the active Territory Model to align with the simplified, matrix-based security architecture.

To balance global visibility with strict Business Unit (BU) editing control, the solution leverages a combination of standard ETM sharing to grant baseline access, paired with Custom Validation Rules and Dynamic Forms to enforce business logic.

OWD Setup Foundation:
Account: Private
Contact: Private
Opportunity: Private
Case: Private
ETM Default Access Levels:
The standard Territory Model configuration must be set as follows to ensure users can access records to trigger the necessary BU validation checks.

Object Access	Standard ETM Configuration Setting	Rationale
Account Access	View and edit accounts assigned to the territory.	Standard native behavior allowing territory members to manage the assigned customer record.
Contact Access	View and edit all contacts associated with accounts in the territory.	Native Simplification: Leverages built-in ETM functionality to grant blanket read/edit access to contacts, removing the need for custom ContactShare flows.
Opportunity & Case Access	View and edit all opportunities/cases associated with accounts in the territory.	Crucial for UI/UX & Validation: ETM must grant standard Read/Write access so users can enter the edit context. Actual saving of the record will be strictly governed by Validation Rules (verifying User BU vs. Record BU), while Lightning Record Pages (Dynamic Forms) will dynamically hide edit actions for non-matching BUs to prevent user frustration.
Hierarchy Access Settings	Opportunity Access for Parent Territories: Must be set to View and edit all opportunities..	Similar to default access, this opens the record up for the validation rules to do their job based on the user's assigned Business Unit.
Enforcement Mechanisms
While ETM opens the record for viewing and potential editing, the following mechanisms secure the matrix:

Validation Rules: Enforced at the database level. A rule on the Opportunity, Case, and Order objects will block the ISNEW() or ISCHANGED() actions if the executing User's assigned Business Unit does not match the record's specified Business Unit.

Lightning Record Pages: To optimize the User Experience, Dynamic Forms and conditionally visible actions will be implemented using Custom Permissions. If a user lacks the Custom Permission for a specific BU, the 'Edit' buttons and editable fields will be hidden from the UI, aligning visual permissions with backend validation.
